The paper deals with the algorithmic study of anti-powers in strings, which involves combinatorial and computational aspects. The most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as the paper describes an optimal algorithm for locating all substrings of a string that are anti-powers of a specified order. The paper also involves combinatorial aspects, which makes cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) another likely category. The study of anti-powers involves the analysis of the structure of strings, which makes cs.CC (Computational Complexity) a possible category. The paper also involves the analysis of the number of distinct anti-powers of a given order, which makes cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) another possible category. Finally, the study of anti-powers involves geometric considerations, which makes cs.CG (Computational Geometry) a possible category.
